  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">SPIRITUAL GIFT<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Paul&rsquo;s Teaching<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:3 Therefore I want you to understand that no one speaking by the Spirit of God ever says &quot;Jesus be cursed!&quot; and no one can say &quot;Jesus is Lord&quot; except by the Holy Spirit.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:4 Now there are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:5 and there are varieties of service, but the same Lord;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:6 and there are varieties of working, but it is the same God who inspires them all in every one.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:7 To each is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the common good.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:8 To one is given through the Spirit the utterance of wisdom, and to another the utterance of knowledge according to the same Spirit,<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:9 to another faith by the same Spirit, to another gifts of healing by the one Spirit,<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:10 to another the working of miracles, to another prophecy, to another the ability to distinguish between spirits, to another various kinds of tongues, to another the interpretation of tongues.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:12 For just as the body is one and has many members, and all the members of the body, though many, are one body, so it is with Christ.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Hierarchy of Spiritual Gift<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1Co 12:28 And God has appointed in the church first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then workers of miracles, then healers, helpers, administrators, speakers in various kinds of tongues.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">According to Corinthians, the same spirit gives varieties of gifts while the same Lord gives varieties of<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. service B. prophecy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. working D. healing.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Option A<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Reference: 1 Cor. 12 : 4 &ndash; 5<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">[4] Now there are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit;&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">[5] and there are varieties of service, but the same Lord;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The first and second in the order of hierarchy of spiritual gifts enumerated by Paul are:<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. healers and helpers&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. teachers and workers of miracles<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. apostles and prophets<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. administrators and speakers<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Option C<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Reference: 1 Cor. 12: 28<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">[28] And God has appointed in the church first apostles, second prophets, third teachers, then workers of miracles, then healers, helpers, administrators, speakers in various kinds of tongues.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Paul teaches that the exercise of spiritual gifts by individual believers should be used to promote<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. co-operation B. knowledge<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. faith D. competition.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. co-operation<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Examples<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Paul declares that Christians have the same functions, but they have gifts that differ according to<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. their devotion to prayer<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. enablement by the spirit<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. their suffering and endurance<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. grace given to them<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. grace given to them<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "SPIRITUAL GIFT"
}